name: Grady - halloween can't come soon enough

metadata.description: i hadn't seen her in six weeks, and she was planning on coming to LA for Halloween. i wrote this right before she got here.

lyrics.text:
You’re on my mind like a thumbtack 

I hope the distance don’t kill us slow

give me that

Same energy when you come back

Where’s this all heading baby?

I really don’t know

But I’m gonna find out love 

I’m gonna find out love 

I’m gonna find out love 

Out love 

I’m never running out of love 

I’m never running out of love 

I’m never running out of love 

And that’s my promise 

You asked for my heart and baby girl you got it 

It’ll be six weeks that I’m living without your body 

Halloween can’t come soon enough 

Halloween can’t come soon enough 

Halloween can’t come soon enough 

I know you’re not the romantic type 

But you still like a dinner out with candle light 

Insecurities, know we all have got a few

But I love your ass and I’ma make you love it too

Everybody’s playing dress up 

Call me babe, I wanna catch up

I know you’re an awful texter

There’s typos every time 

Still don’t know what I’m gonna be 

Coming with your girls, but you go with me 

You know you always got a home with me 

That’s my promise 

You asked for my heart and baby girl you got it 

It’ll be six weeks that I’m living without your body 

Halloween can’t come soon enough 

Halloween can’t come soon enough 

Halloween can’t come soon enough
